  "prompt": "What are Some interesting facts of Langar at golden temple?",
  "response": "Here are some interesting facts about Langar at the Golden Temple (Harmandir Sahib) in Amritsar, Punjab:\n\n1. Scale of Operation\n- Serves free meals to 100,000-300,000 people daily\n- Operates 24 hours a day\n- Largest free community kitchen in the world\n\n2. Volunteer-based Kitchen\n- Completely run by volunteers (Sewadars)\n- People from all backgrounds and religions participate in cooking and serving\n\n3. Food Preparation\n- Vegetarian meals are served\n- Cooking is done using large industrial-sized vessels\n- Wheat flour is kneaded and chapatis are made by hand\n\n4. Equality and Inclusivity\n- Everyone sits on the floor together\n- No discrimination based on caste, religion, gender, or economic status\n- People eat together as a community\n\n5. Historical Significance\n- Started by Guru Nanak Dev Ji in the 16th century\n- Reflects Sikh principles of community service and equality\n\n6. Infrastructure\n- Massive kitchen with multiple cooking stations\n- Advanced food preparation and distribution systems\n- Highly organized and efficient\n\n7. Funding\n- Entirely funded by voluntary donations\n- No government or external funding\n\nThese facts highlight the remarkable humanitarian and community-oriented aspect of Langar at the Golden Temple.",
